<exercise checkit-seed="0004" checkit-slug="TI1" checkit-title="Substitution method">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Explain how to find the anti-derivative of <m>f(x)=\frac{4 \, \cos\left(x\right)}{\sin\left(x\right)}</m>.
                    
                </p>
                
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    Explain how to evaluate the following definite integral:
                    <me>
                        \int_{ \frac{1}{9} \, \pi }^{ \frac{1}{2} \, \pi } \cos\left(3 \, x\right) dx.
                    </me>
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
        
        
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <m>\displaystyle \int \frac{4 \, \cos\left(x\right)}{\sin\left(x\right)} dx=4 \, \log\left(\sin\left(x\right)\right)+C.</m>
                </p>
                
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
                    <m>\displaystyle \int_{ \frac{1}{9} \, \pi }^{ \frac{1}{2} \, \pi } \cos\left(3 \, x\right) dx = -\frac{1}{6} \, \sqrt{3} - \frac{1}{3}.</m>
                </p>
                
            </li>
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
